-- Former BES CEO Salgado taken to court, to appear before judge -official
-- 
-- Thu Jul 24, 2014 05:11AM EDT
-- None



LISBON, July 24 (Reuters) - Ricardo Espirito Santo Salgado, the patriarch of Portugal's troubled Espirito Santo banking family and former CEO of Banco Espirito Santo <BES.LS>, was detained by law officials on Thursday and will appear before a judge, a court official in Lisbon said.

"Ricardo Salgado was brought to the court by representatives of the prosecutor's office and will appear before a judge later today," the duty official at the Central Criminal Custody Court told Reuters, without elaborating.